18. Trends I see? Expectation of reflationary policies pushing US dollar up, which creates headwinds against any efforts to stimulate demand
17. Trends I see? Inflation gradually gaining momentum but still historically low. No immediate pressure on Fed to act.

14. And let us always remember, monthly data can be choppy and liable to revision. So we should focus on trends, not one-off.

12. Of course, gains in jobs, wages, and participation will also make the Fed more likely to push back on growth by raising rates.
